ALL clarity/bard songs/etc), double damage, spells that take 1/2 mana, etc as a starting point.  What do you all think of this?<br>
<br>
Niam D'Sparil<br>
Wizard, 55th Circle<br>
Clan Icewind <br>
Zebsuxor Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalamberih.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MalamberIH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 5:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> We get spells after 50th level, other classes get Disciplines.  Nice idea, but I can tell you that'll never fly. <p><p><font color="#FFFFFF"><b><em><font size="4">Malamber</font></em> </b> of Erollisi Marr<br> 
51st Channeler</font></p> 

<p> </p> 

<p><i><font color="#FFFFFF">"There are five ways of attacking with fire.  The first is to burn
soldiers in their camp;<BR>the second is to burn stores; the third is to burn
baggage trains; <BR>the fourth is to burn arsenals and magazines; <BR>
the fifth is to hurl dropping fire amongst the enemy. "</font></i></p> 

<p><font size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><i>--Sun Tsu</i></font></p> 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyght.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myght</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 5:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> hybrids get spells after 50 and also get disciplines (4 discs each).<br>
<br>
i dont see anything too unbalancing with us getting one or two disciplines post 50 with *long* reload time (which we would save for the 'uber' encounters.<br>
<br>
that would sorta solve us being more effective in those fights, while not being too powerful during casual groups.<br>
<br>
we get new spells post 50, but *many* of them are pretty useless (alkabor spells, flaming sword, plainsight (stackign issues), etc) <p>Myght 
<br>
Sorcerer
<br>
Tides of Destiny
<br> 
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 410<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 9:17 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> Would it be nice?  Of course.  However we already know the response.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Disciplines were not meant for pure casters.  They aren't in the game now.  They will never be in the game.  Why?  Because we SAID so thats why.&quot;<br>
<br>
Does that quote even slightly ring true?<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 10:27 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> I had suggested something like these back in the class talks and Absor blew me off. <br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
