Call of Ascension<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 11:07 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> I am sure you weren't surprised by the response at all.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urochenko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rochenko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 2:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> What about a discipline of focus?<br>
i.e. for a brief period...(30 seconds, one minute maybe) every spell we cast specialization automatically kicks in.  This is more along the lines of melee discs.  It takes a skill they already have and makes it work for sure.  This would help out on mana savings without unbalancing us.<br>
<br>
Hraveob Boevarh<br>
Gnomish ICBM of Lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 450<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 8:42 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disciplines?</span><hr size=1> Aye, another suggestion that has had variation brought forth.  I think it is as useful now as it was before.  I just wish they would even entertain the possibility.<br>
